<article id="post-2873" class="post-2873 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-future-we-want tag-films tag-oceans tag-sustainable-development">
	<header class="entry-header">
		<h1 class="entry-title">Special event: Planet Ocean film screening</h1>

				<div class="entry-meta">
			<span class="sep">Posted on </span><a href="http://blogs.un.org/blog/2013/09/11/special-event-planet-ocean-film-screening/" title="5:05 PM" rel="bookmark"><time class="entry-date" datetime="2013-09-11T17:05:41+00:00">September 11, 2013</time></a><span class="by-author"> <span class="sep"> by </span> <span class="author vcard"><a class="url fn n" href="http://blogs.un.org/blog/author/nancygroves/" title="View all posts by Social Media Team" rel="author">Social Media Team</a></span></span>		</div><!-- .entry-meta -->
			</header><!-- .entry-header -->

	<div class="entry-content">
		<p style="text-align: center"><span class="vvqbox vvqyoutube" style="width:425px;height:344px;"><span id="vvq-2873-youtube-1"><a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=7vYMUV2_das" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push(['_trackEvent','outbound-article','http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=7vYMUV2_das']);"><img src="http://i0.wp.com/img.youtube.com/vi/7vYMUV2_das/0.jpg?w=584" alt="YouTube Preview Image" data-recalc-dims="1" /></a></span></span></p>
<p><a href="http://www.unep.org/" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push(['_trackEvent','outbound-article','http://www.unep.org/']);">UN Environment Programme (UNEP)</a> Goodwill Ambassador, Yann Arthus-Bertrand, photographer, filmmaker, and philanthropist, screened his film, <em>Planet Ocean</em> to the United Nations community on Wednesday.</p>
<p><a href="http://bit.ly/1d6veLA" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push(['_trackEvent','outbound-article','http://bit.ly/1d6veLA']);">UN Secretary-General Ban Ki-moon opened the event</a> and made introductory remarks at the film’s New York debut.</p>
<p>Co-directed by Michael Pitiot, narrated by Josh Duhamel, <em>Planet Ocean</em> features dazzling aerial and underwater imagery to deliver a far-reaching assessment of the political and environmental challenges facing our oceans, including over-fishing, pollution and climate change.</p>
<p>The film has been financed by OMEGA. The firm has long been associated with the planet’s oceans and understands the dangers facing them, as well as the importance of their preservation. The <a href="http://www.omegawatches.com/spirit/social-responsibility/planet-ocean" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push(['_trackEvent','outbound-article','http://www.omegawatches.com/spirit/social-responsibility/planet-ocean']);">partnership between OMEGA and <em>Planet Ocean</em></a> was created in the spirit of its support for late friend and brand ambassador Sir Peter Blake and its decades-long sport of oceanic health and exploration.</p>
<p><img class="aligncenter" alt="" src="http://i2.wp.com/www.unric.org/en/images/stories/cine-onu/planetocean.jpg?resize=470%2C664" data-recalc-dims="1" /></p>
<p>Related content</p>
<ul>
<li><a href="http://www.un.org/en/sustainablefuture/oceans.shtml" >The Future We Want: Oceans</a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.un.org/depts/los/reference_files/worldoceansday.htm" >World Oceans Day</a></li>
</ul>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
